attributes.title: Customers: APIM Call Count By Time

attributes.description:
This report helps in visualizing the call count aggregated by the exec_time over a period of time.
The aggregation is on 
- exec_time <0.8s
- exec_time >=0.8 and exec_time <2
- exec_time>=2 and exec_time<5
- exec_time>=5
- 

Filters
- By customer - Add a filter "customer_name:Google"
- By customer and unsuccessful calls - Add a filter "customer_name:Google AND status>399 AND status<600"
attributes.title: Call count aggregated by exec_time in a Time Series

attributes.description:
This report depicts the % of calls processed in a given range of execution time.
Execution time is the total processing time taken by the traffic manager. It is measured from the time the first byte is received to the very last byte sent in the response.

Filters
- By uri - Add a filter like uri:/va/offers/faresbestprices/bestfares"
- By customer - Add a filter like "customer_name:Google"
- By successful calls for a given uri - Add a filter like "uri:/v1/offers AND status<400"
attributes.title: Call Distribution by execution time buckets

attributes.description:
Shows the call count aggregated by server_name over a period of time.

Filters
- By customer - Add a filter "customer_name:Google" to view all server_name for a given customer
- By customer and successful calls - Add a filter "customer_name:Google AND status>=200 AND status<400
- By successful calls - Add a filter "status>=200 AND status<400
- By unsuccessfil calls - Add a filter "status>=400 and status<600
attributes.title: Call count aggregated by request_host_name in a time series

attributes.description:
This visualization shows the count aggregated by URI over a period of time.

Filters
- By customer: To get list of top 10 uri's called by customer add the filter "customer_name:Google"
- By proxy_worker: To get a list of top 10 uri's serviced by a proxy worker, add the filter proxy_worker:<name of the worker>

attributes.description:
Shows a list of customer with call count with % share in a descending order.

By adding filters like 
- server_name:"api-music.rovicorp.com"
- status:200  
- status>399 OR status<600 
you can get a count aggregated by URI

The report can be downloaded as a comma separated values (csv) as well.
